    "To facilitate this, we divided each dataset into two parts -a training set and a test set.",
    "Given the variation in the number of images across the different datasets, we randomly generated the training and test sets for each dataset.In order to verify the effectiveness of the proposed model, we conducted a comparison with several existing remote sensing image scene classification methods.",
    "These include, CaffeNet [13], GoogleNet [13], VGG16 [13], DBN [37] GCFs+LOFs [38], Deep Filter Banks [39], RSSCNet [40], GCNN [41], ETDL [43] pre-trained ResNet-34 [40], and MTLS [44] Performance analysis Experimental results on different datasetThis section tests the proposed strategy's efficancy on different datasets, including RSSCN7, PatternNet, and Eurosat datasets, to investigate its robustness and generalization.",
    "The performance comparison results for RSSCN7 dataset are presented in Table 1.",
    "According to Our model attains 97% accuracy in 7 categories, and most categories obtain more than 95% accuracy."
